    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "## Problem\n\nFlakey tests are painful to track and it's difficult to correlate when a test started becoming unreliable. Also hard to correlate increases in CI time-cost.\n\n## Proposal\n\nAutomate storage of a json file with CI + test stats.\nDisplay it here?\n\nOr maybe this can be done in a branch on the main neovim repo, as a jupyter notebook or something like that.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Probably the easiest approach to this would be:\n\n- In neovim/neovim have a script that generates the plots and tables (e.g. in markdown format)\n- That script is called from the gendoc.lua script in neovim/neovim.github.io and gets build to a page `/ci-stats` or whatever.\n\nNote: if going the jupyter notebook route, do note these can be exported to html. Otherwise `pd.to_markdown()` and `plt.savefig('name.svg')` are really useful.",
