            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> if going the jupyter notebook route, do note these can be exported to html.\n\nyeah, also I think github can display them \"natively\", which is very nice and saves a lot of work.\n\n\n> That script is called from the gendoc.lua script in neovim/neovim.github.io and gets build to a page `/ci-stats` or whatever.\n\nThat reminds me, one reason we had neovim/doc was to avoid clobbering \"real\" repos with many GB of data. However, we can avoid blowing up the neovim/neovim.github.io repo size by (1) committing to a separate branch and (2) force-pushing to delete old history.",
