            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> That reminds me, one reason we had neovim/doc was to avoid clobbering \"real\" repos with many GB of data. However, we can avoid blowing up the neovim/neovim.github.io repo size by (1) committing to a separate branch and (2) force-pushing to delete old history.\n\nI don't see how this would be a problem if the files are never commited to the repo: current `/doc/user/` pages are also generated on the fly in CI and deployed to GH pages. Not included in the repo. \n\nEDIT: ah okay if you want to display the notebooks on GitHub then yes a separate branch might be a good idea. ",
